"&#xa0;\nOAR0006Written evidence submitted by the National Deaf Children’s Society (NDCS) &#xa0;\nExecutive summary &#xa0;\nNDCS is concerned that Ofsted inspections and its annual report do not sufficiently emphasise the importance of local authority specialist SEN support services for deaf children. \n&#xa0;\nA failure to inspect or scrutinise or even comment on these services sends \na signal that these services are not important, when many deaf children and their families rely on these services to achieve good outcomes. \n&#xa0;\nIntroduction &#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nEnsuring specialist SEN support services for children are fit for purpose&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n“There was limited strategic overview and no systematic approach across all services to evaluate the quality of services and their impact on improving the lives\n of deaf children.”\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nChildren and Families Bill &#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nRecommendations &#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nPossible questions to raise &#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nJanuary 2014\n              \n              \n              \n              \n&#xa0;\n"